name: Winchester 1873
description: The Winchester Model 1873 is an American lever-action repeating rifle produced from 1873 to 1919 by the Winchester Repeating Arms Company. The second iteration of the Winchester rifle, the Model 1873 was a refinement of the Model 1866; marketed as "the Gun that Won the West", the rifle, as with its predecessor, the Model 1866, was an instant success, with over 720,000 produced over its lifespan.
